name: CultivestPortfolioNFT

methods.name: mintPortfolio

args.name: owner
args.desc: - The Algorand address that will own this portfolio token

methods.desc: Mint new portfolio token for a user

methods.name: addPositionToPortfolio
methods.desc:
Add position token to a portfolio token
Properly stores the mapping on-chain using box storage

methods.name: removePositionFromPortfolio
methods.desc:
Remove position token from a portfolio token
Properly removes the on-chain mapping

methods.name: getPositionPortfolio
methods.desc: Get which portfolio id a position belongs to. Returns 0 if the position is not assigned to any portfolio

methods.name: getPortfolioPositionCount
methods.desc: Get number of positions in a portfolio

methods.name: getPortfolioPositionIds
methods.desc:
Get all position IDs in a portfolio (packed as bytes)
Returns packed array of uint64 position IDs
Each position ID is 8 bytes, so divide length by 8 to get count

methods.name: updatePortfolio
methods.desc: Update portfolio token values and performance

methods.name: portfolioExists
methods.desc: Check if portfolio token ID is valid (read-only)

desc:
Cultivest Portfolio NFT Smart Contract
Mints individual portfolio tokens that reference Position NFT token IDs
Each portfolio token represents a collection of position tokens owned by a user

Uses box storage to maintain on-chain mappings of positions to portfolios

sourceInfo.errorMessage: Portfolio has no positions to remove
Position already assigned to a portfolio
can only call when not creating
